The paper is about techniques for speeding up the test-time evaluation of large convolutional networks designed for object recognition tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of state-of-the-art models and techniques for reducing computation, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of linear structure within convolutional filters, which is a topic that falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the computation required for evaluating convolutional layers, which is a topic that falls under the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
